@Node "Arexx function PRINT" "dfa_english.guide/Arexx function PRINT"
@Next "Arexx function SAVE"
@Prev "Arexx function PREVSEL"
@Toc "The Arexx Commands"

PRINT
-----

Syntax:
     PRINT WHICH/K, FILE/K, NLQ/S, CONDENSED/S, FORMFEED/S, FORM/N
          WHICH         `WHICH' can get the following assignments:
          
                        ALL       All addresses are printed
                        SELECTED  Only the marked addresses are printed
                        ACTIVE    The active item (if there is one) is
                                  printed
          
          FILE          If you give `FILE' together with a filename
                        the addresses are not printed to the printer, but
                        to the file.
          NLQ           The addresses are printed in `N'ear `L'etter `Q'uality.
          CONDENSED     The addresses are printed in condensed mode
          FORMFEED      Afted the last address printed a formfeed is performed.
                        Notice that the setting from the print window is 
                        *not* used here!
          FORM          `Form' can be assigned to the numbers `0' to `4'.
                        These numbers are (nearly) the same as in the `Print' window.
                        The difference is that here the first number is `0'
                        instead of `1':
          
                        0:    Short address list
                        1:    Long address list
                        2:    Phone list
                        3:    Mailing labels
                        4:    Address cards


Return value:
     Error code in RC

Function:
     The desired addresses are printed.


@EndNode

@Node "Arexx function SAVE" "dfa_english.guide/Arexx function SAVE"
@Next "Arexx function SAVEAS"
